node.text: Here’s a little sneak peek into our flight with @etihadairways inside ‘The Residence’. This was our last flight of the year and was such an amazing way to close out the decade, after such incredible adventures! Truly a once in a lifetime experience that we’ll never forget. #Etihad #A380 #sponsored

node.text: #WCOxTaraMilkTea ✨ Created for the wanderlust dreamers, it felt so special to be wearing my collection pieces for our final trip of the year (and the decade) in one of the most beautiful places on earth. These pieces mean so much to me and have been all around the world for the last half year, and I’m excited to wear them well into the new decade. @wanderlustandco ✨

node.text: Silver Birch in the Autumn breeze. 🍂 The leaves on these trees are harvested in the Summer time (when they are green) for some of @Jurlique’s signature products. 🍃 Birch leaves possess purifying, softening, and soothing properties and can be found in Radiant Skin Foaming Cleanser, Revitalising Cleansing Gel, Replenishing Cleansing Lotion and Nourishing Cleansing Oil! #Jurlique #ad

node.text: Plucking daisies on the @Jurlique farm. 🌼😌🌼 Over fifty kilograms of daisies will be harvested from this very patch this season! A fun fact about daisies is that the extract helps rebalance oiliness and boost radiance. It helps improve luminosity and uneven skin tone, and refreshes and calms the skin. 😮 The ingredient can be found in Jurlique’s hand wash too. 🥰🧼 #Jurlique #ad

node.text: We managed to catch Autumn in all it’s glory on the stunning @Jurlique farm in South Australia. 🍁🍂 I've wanted to visit this place for years. I was able to see and learn about all of the pure botanicals that go into the beautiful Jurlique products - including Jurlique's famous Radiance blend of Lavender, Rose gallica, Calendula & Marshmallow Root, known for their naturally hydrating properties. Excited to show you more from our time here. ✨ #Jurlique #ad
